	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jun 12th 10:56 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have a Tolap Robe.&nbsp;&nbsp;I like it quite a bit.  Eventually when I upgrade this baby i'm thinking of twinking a nooby Necro.  For us higher level casters.. the Haste really has no benefit.  <br><br>I always wondered why that effect was put on it to begin with.  A nooby caster starting from scratch could really tear up the snakes and bats with this robe. ;P Its a twink item.  Still.. I do use it as a greenie squisher.  Pop my old weapon in hand and a hasted caster can squish greenies .. heh.. sorta ok.<br><br>The stats are decent though. STR is alwasy desirable for a caster as they are weak to begin with.  The INT at +10 is very nice, and +50 mana is most welcome.  The +5 wis.. maybe not a serious benefit for a Wizard, but still.. stat boosters are stat boosters.<br><br>Has anyone figure out what % haste this Robe is? I'm wondering if its like a RBG or more like an FBSS.. or if its just tagged haste to make us feel cool.<br><br>Dolo, 53.956034 Wizzy<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
