	   <tr><td colspan=2>Any class can make use of haste.&nbsp;&nbsp;2 [more or less] pure casters of note that can make very good use of a haste item is a druid and a shaman.  My druid has 900 ac self buffed, that's equivelant to a well equipped upper 40's and decently equipped lower 50's ranger/warrior (depending on the levels of either) and shaman break 1000ac fairly easy being the types of armor and buffs they have.  It's nice to be able to clear a greenie that jumps you without having to burn mana by just beating it sensless as well as saves you a lot of downtime.  This robe is somewhat of a bonus for achieving 55+ as a pure caster as it gives you the ability to melee a little instead of having to sit and cast all the time, just a perk more than anything.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
